<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00096</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT AUTHORIZING THE CITY OR MUNICIPAL CIVIL REGISTRAR, OR THE CONSUL GENERAL, TO UPDATE IN THE CIVIL REGISTER THE CIVIL STATUS OF A FILIPINO SPOUSE WHO WAS VALIDLY DIVORCED BY A FOREIGN SPOUSE, WITHOUT THE NEED OF A JUDICIAL ORDER</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : "Foreign Divorce Recognition Act"
Authorizes the city or civil registrar, or the consul general, to update in the civil register the civil status of a Filipino spouse who was validly divorced by a foreign spouse, without the need of a judicial order.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ACOSTA-ALBA, MA. LOURDES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Flores (000 2019-08-22)</td><td>2. Fortun (000 2019-09-12)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON POPULATION AND FAMILY RELATIONS ON 2019-07-23</td></tr></table>